to find me alive.

63
00:10:57,180 --> 00:11:00,013
Everyone in our family
died while in good health.

64
00:11:00,340 --> 00:11:03,138
My mother, and yours also.

65
00:11:03,420 --> 00:11:05,058
It's about my will.

66
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:11,416
Auntie!

67
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:29,650
Weronika, get up.
The lawyer is here.

68
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:42,712
Weronika?

69
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:43,432
Yes...

70
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:44,916
It's Weronika.

71
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,631
My God! You're here?

72
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:48,636
I'm here.

73
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:50,269
Here, in Krakow?

74
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:51,117
Right here.

75
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,155
A week now.

76
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:55,510
Really! Will you come see me?

77
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:57,233
Of course.

78
00:11:58,080 --> 00:12:00,310
Today at rehearsal.
At two o'clock.

79
00:12:02,220 --> 00:12:03,289
At rehearsal?

80
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:10,039
Good. That's how it should sound.

81
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:12,354
Once more, please.

82
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:51,036
Thank you.
See you tomorrow.

83
