It's so complicated.

291
00:58:04,420 --> 00:58:05,648
What are you doing?

292
00:58:06,460 --> 00:58:07,939
I'm turning myself in. That's all.

293
00:58:08,420 --> 00:58:09,136
I'm sorry.

294
00:58:23,660 --> 00:58:24,297
Daddy...

295
00:58:36,020 --> 00:58:37,339
I'm in the bathtub.

296
00:58:57,980 --> 00:58:59,254
Don't touch the chairs!

297
00:59:14,180 --> 00:59:15,090
Try this.

298
00:59:24,020 --> 00:59:24,896
It's nice.

299
00:59:26,180 --> 00:59:28,011
The other one was more pleasant.

300
00:59:28,940 --> 00:59:31,534
This is from the end of autumn,
the other was from the beginning.

301
00:59:33,580 --> 00:59:37,095
I don't know if people will need
this fragrance, but we'll see.

302
00:59:38,260 --> 00:59:39,375
I'll get dressed.

303
00:59:40,620 --> 00:59:42,690
Have you understood, at last?

304
00:59:46,060 --> 00:59:47,539
There's a letter for you.

305
00:59:50,980 --> 00:59:51,969
Beautiful handwriting.

306
01:00:14,660 --> 01:00:15,410
Here?

307
01:00:17,100 --> 01:00:17,737
No.

308
01:00:19,740 --> 01:00:22,049
You'll stay? We'll fix lunch...

309
01:00:22,260 --> 01:00:24,091
No, I have to go.
I have a music class.

310
01:00:27,220 --> 01:00:28,699
I must have dreamt it.

311
01:00:31,700 --> 01:00:33,019
I saw a drawing...

312
01:00:34,300 --> 01:00:35,972
very simple, even naive.

313
01:00:37,660 --> 01:00:40,333
A sloping road in a small town...

314
01:00:41,860 --> 01:00:43,532
lined on both sides by houses...

315
01:00:44,940 --> 01:00:47,090
with a church in the background.

316
01:00:49,060 --> 01:00:49,810
Chagall?

317
01:00:52,740 --> 01:00:54,059
No, not Chagall.

318
01:00:54,580 --> 01:00:57,094
A tall, slender church,
made of red brick...

319
01:01:05,140 --> 01:01:07,256
Stop. Nicole, you're playing off-key.

320
01:01:07,660 --> 01:01:08,775
Yes, I know.

321
01:01:15,900 --> 01:01:18,368
Fine, let's start again.

322
01:01:38,560 --> 01:01:40,536
Nicole! Stop.

323
01:03:40,860 --> 01:03:42,418
Your attention, please.

324
01:03:42,620 --> 01:03:45,532
Miss Sandrine Ekar,

325
01:03:45,780 --> 01:03:47,498
please come to the reception desk
at gate...

326
01:03:58,900 --> 01:03:59,935
Excuse me, excuse me.

327
01:04:18,100 --> 01:04:19,897
Attention, please.

328
01:04:20,100 --> 01:04:22,534
Train number 3316

329
01:04:22,740 --> 01:04:24,776
from Cherbourg

330
01:04:24,980 --> 01:04:27,892
is arriving on platform 18.

331
01:05:04,020 --> 01:05:04,975
Who's there?

332
01:07:58,680 --> 01:08:01,114
Excuse me... is there another cafe
in this station?

333
01:08:01,320 --> 01:08:02,116
Over there.

334
01:08:04,360 --> 01:08:07,636
Can you hear the loudspeaker there?
For the train departures?

335
01:08:07,960 --> 01:08:09,916
I don't know.
I was never there.

336
01:08:11,240 --> 01:08:11,877
Thank you.

337
01:09:45,680 --> 01:09:46,635
Excuse me, excuse me.

338
01:10:38,640 --> 01:10:39,755
Would you like some tea?

339
01:10:42,200 --> 01:10:43,076
Coffee.

340
01:10:44,740 --> 01:10:45,252
Please...

341
01:10:45,460 --> 01:10:46,415
Tea with lemon?

342
01:10:47,300 --> 01:10:48,255
And one coffee.

343
01:10:59,140 --> 01:10:59,856
"Stop".

344
01:11:17,700 --> 01:11:19,497
Have you been waiting long?

345
01:11:23,340 --> 01:11:24,409
48 hours.

346
01:11:25,980 --> 01:11:27,049
Maybe longer.

347
01:11:43,780 --> 01:11:44,974
It was worth it.

348
01:11:54,380 --> 01:11:55,369
I have to apologize.

349
01:11:55,580 --> 01:11:56,410
For what?

350
01:11:58,100 --> 01:11:59,613
I was afraid you wouldn't come.

351
01:12:02,820 --> 01:12:03,775
I was afraid

352
01:12:04,100 --> 01:12:05,089
you wouldn't be here.

353
01:12:05,860 --> 01:12:07,088
I had to be here.

354
01:12:09,460 --> 01:12:10,210
I would have waited for you

355
01:12:10,460 --> 01:12:11,415
two more days...

356
01:12:12,900 --> 01:12:13,616
or three.

357
01:12:17,660 --> 01:12:19,059
I wanted to be sure...

358
01:12:20,100 --> 01:12:21,897
I wanted to see if it was possible.

359
01:12:24,420 --> 01:12:25,489
Be sure of what?

360
01:12:27,220 --> 01:12:28,335
Whether it was possible...

361
01:12:28,580 --> 01:12:29,649
psychologically.

362
01:12:33,300 --> 01:12:36,019
If what was psychologically
possible?

363
01:12:45,820 --> 01:12:48,573
Since you're here, you must know
that I write children's books.

364
01:12:51,300 --> 01:12:53,814
But now I want to write a book...

365
01:12:54,860 --> 01:12:55,815
a real book.

366
01:12:59,260 --> 01:13:00,978
In this book there's a woman...

367
01:13:03,380 --> 01:13:06,417
a woman who responds
to the call of an unknown man.

368
01:13:08,180 --> 01:13:10,375
So I wondered whether
that was possible.

369
01:13:11,500 --> 01:13:14,094
Whether, psychologically, a woman...

370
01:13:15,780 --> 01:13:17,771
Well, whether it was possible.

371
01:13:24,380 --> 01:13:25,449
You're not saying anything?

372
01:13:31,620 --> 01:13:32,530
Why me?

373
01:13:33,420 --> 01:13:35,058
Why did you choose me?

374
01:13:36,980 --> 01:13:38,049
Because...

375
01:13:41,660 --> 01:13:42,570
I don't know.

376
01:13:47,780 --> 01:13:48,974
Thanks for the coffee.

377
01:16:41,660 --> 01:16:42,775
Wait, please!

378
01:17:04,900 --> 01:17:07,858
Are there any rooms
facing the back? I'm exhausted.

379
01:17:10,060 --> 01:17:11,652
Sure. What floor?

380
01:17:12,260 --> 01:17:13,488
As long as it's quiet.

381
01:17:15,980 --> 01:17:18,289
Number 287.
You want a wake-up call?

382
01:17:18,500 --> 01:17:19,728
No, thank you.

383
01:17:45,820 --> 01:17:46,889
I'm sorry.

384
01:17:50,060 --> 01:17:51,334
Please forgive me.

385
01:17:54,000 --> 01:17:55,611
For what?

386
01:21:17,060 --> 01:21:19,449
As I was falling asleep
I saw a aheet floating down.

387
01:21:22,460 --> 01:21:23,449
I love you.

388
01:21:27,060 --> 01:21:28,015
I love you.

389
01:21:55,180 --> 01:21:57,171
What else do you want to know
about me?

390
01:22:01,820 --> 01:22:02,457
Everything.

391
01:22:34,620 --> 01:22:35,609
What's this?

392
01:22:37,660 --> 01:22:39,616
For when I have chapped lips.

393
01:22:45,340 --> 01:22:46,170
Shit!

394
01:22:48,500 --> 01:22:50,252
I've been looking for
those for a year!

395
01:23:11,060 --> 01:23:11,810
Véronique...

396
01:23:12,900 --> 01:23:13,457
Yes?

397
01:23:15,940 --> 01:23:16,895
I know now why

398
01:23:18,180 --> 01:23:19,295
you were the one.

399
01:23:21,780 --> 01:23:22,417
Yes.

400
01:23:25,420 --> 01:23:26,614
It was not the book.

401
01:23:33,300 --> 01:23:34,528
I knew it.

402
01:23:37,020 --> 01:23:37,657
- What?

403
01:23:37,860 --> 01:23:39,691
- Why you were doing it.

404
01:23:41,020 --> 01:23:43,170
Since the first night you called me.

405
01:23:44,180 --> 01:23:45,169
Even before that.

406
01:23:47,540 --> 01:23:48,416
You knew?

407
01:23:51,220 --> 01:23:51,811
Everything.

408
01:23:57,060 --> 01:23:59,654
This may have nothing to do with it,
or it may.

409
01:24:00,860 --> 01:24:04,057
All my live I've felt I was
in two places at the same time.

410
01:24:05,060 --> 01:24:06,413
Here and somewhere alse.

411
01:24:08,700 --> 01:24:09,849
It's hard to explain.

412
01:24:11,380 --> 01:24:12,415
But I know...

413
01:24:13,700 --> 01:24:15,656
I always sense what I have to do.

414
01:24:28,380 --> 01:24:29,495
Where is this?

415
01:24:30,020 --> 01:24:31,135
It's not in France.

416
01:24:32,740 --> 01:24:35,937
That's during a trip
to Czechoslovakia, Hungary, Poland.

417
01:24:36,900 --> 01:24:38,413
That must be in Krakow.

418
01:24:43,180 --> 01:24:44,852
That's a beautiful photograph.

419
01:24:47,660 --> 01:24:49,457
And you, in that huge coat.

420
01:24:56,540 --> 01:24:57,495
That's not me.

421
01:24:59,940 --> 01:25:01,009
Sure it's you.

422
01:25:18,410 --> 01:25:19,684
That's not my coat.

423
01:30:19,570 --> 01:30:20,889
Is that me?

424
01:30:22,290 --> 01:30:23,325
Of course it's you.

425
01:30:45,650 --> 01:30:46,366
Why..

426
01:30:50,530 --> 01:30:51,519
Why two?

427
01:30:52,650 --> 01:30:54,606
Because during performances
I handle them a lot.

428
01:30:55,850 --> 01:30:57,078
They damage easily.

429
01:31:04,490 --> 01:31:05,081
Try it...

430
01:31:41,850 --> 01:31:43,078
Should I read it to you?

431
01:31:47,250 --> 01:31:49,286
November 23, 1966...

432
01:31:50,490 --> 01:31:52,765
...was the most important day
of their lives.

433
01:31:53,490 --> 01:31:55,799
That day, at theree
in the morning...

434
01:31:56,090 --> 01:31:58,604
...they were both born
in two different cities...

435
01:31:58,810 --> 01:32:00,402
...on two different continents.

436
01:32:01,490 --> 01:32:04,607
They both had dark hair
and brownish-green eyes.

437
01:32:06,570 --> 01:32:09,289
When they were both two years old
and already knew how to walk...

438
01:32:09,930 --> 01:32:12,125
...one of them
burned her han on a stove.

439
01:32:12,890 --> 01:32:14,039
A few days later...

440
01:32:14,490 --> 01:32:16,560
...the other one reached out
to touch the stove...

441
01:32:16,770 --> 01:32:18,567
...but pulled away
just in time.

442
01:32:19,490 --> 01:32:22,607
And yet, she could not have known
that she was about to burn herself.

443
01:32:31,290 --> 01:32:32,086
Do you like it?

444
01:32:36,890 --> 01:32:39,358
I think I'll call it,
"The Double Life of..."

445
01:32:42,050 --> 01:32:43,961
I haven't yet decided
what names to give them.

